## Phase 1 — Project scaffold & type definitions
**Goal:** Runnable Expo project with full TypeScript structure and all shared interfaces defined. No logic yet — just the skeleton everything else will be built on.

```
Using the CLAUDE.md as context, scaffold a new Expo React Native project in TypeScript with the following:

1. Create the full directory structure:
   /src/types, /src/services, /src/components, /src/screens, /src/templates

2. Create /src/types/schemas.ts with strict TypeScript interfaces for:
   - FieldMeasurement: id, schema_version, captured_at (ISO 8601), fields (Record<string, string | number | boolean>), raw_transcript, confidence_score (0–1), validated, synced, optional location (lat, lng)
   - ChecklistEntry: id, checklist_id, step_index, step_label, confirmed, confirmed_at (optional), voice_response, synced
   - FreeformNote: id, captured_at, raw_transcript, synced
   - SyncQueueItem: id, table_name, payload (JSON string), created_at, synced, retry_count, last_error (optional)
   - ParseResult: raw_transcript, confidence_score, parsed_fields (Record<string, string | number | boolean>), flag (optional string), validated

3. Install dependencies: expo-sqlite, @react-native-community/netinfo, expo-haptics, expo-av, @supabase/supabase-js

4. Create empty stub files (no logic, just exports) for all services:
   cactus.ts, sqlite.ts, syncQueue.ts, supabase.ts, validation.ts

5. Create empty stub screens: Home.tsx, Checklist.tsx, History.tsx

6. Verify the project builds and runs with no TypeScript errors.

No `any` types. No logic yet. Types only.
```

