## Phase 6 — VoiceCapture component & core UI shell
**Goal:** The primary UI. One screen, one button, real-time feedback. This is what the judges see.

```
Using CLAUDE.md, implement the VoiceCapture component and Home screen:

/src/components/VoiceCapture.tsx:
1. Large circular button, centred on screen with massive whitespace around it
2. Two states: idle (press to activate) and listening (press again to stop and parse)
3. On first press: call cactus.startListening(), animate button to listening state (subtle pulse — state transition only, no decorative animation), fire haptic via expo-haptics
4. On second press: call cactus.stopAndParse(activeSchema), show loading state as text only ("Parsing..."), never a spinner
5. On parse complete: pass result to validation service, fire haptic on success or failure
6. Display ParsedPreview component below button showing structured JSON result
7. If validation errors exist: display error labels in red beneath each flagged field, speak error via TTS ("Low confidence on fuel level — please repeat")
8. SyncStatus indicator in top right corner — small dot, green when synced, amber when queue has pending items

/src/components/ParsedPreview.tsx:
1. Animated reveal of parsed JSON fields as key-value rows
2. Each row: field name (muted, small) + value (bold, large)
3. Flagged fields highlighted with red left border
4. "Commit" button appears after successful parse — writes to SQLite and queues for sync

/src/screens/Home.tsx:
1. Template selector at top — horizontal scroll of three template pills (Preflight, Crop Scout, Defect Report)
2. Active template name shown below selector
3. VoiceCapture component fills remaining space

Dark mode supported. Monochrome base. SF Pro / Roboto system fonts. Two weights only. No heavy UI libraries.
```

