## Phase 9 — End-to-end integration & demo hardening
**Goal:** Everything wired together, tested offline, sync demonstrated live. This is the demo-ready build.

```
Wire all phases together and harden for the demo:

1. Ensure startSyncMonitor() from syncQueue.ts is called once in the root App.tsx on launch
2. Ensure SQLite is initialised before any screen renders — show a brief "Loading..." text (not a spinner) if model is still loading
3. Test the complete offline loop in airplane mode:
   - Speak a crop scout entry → parse → validate → SQLite write → confirm in History screen
   - Complete the preflight checklist → all steps confirmed → all entries in History
   - Speak a defect report entry with a deliberate out-of-range value → confirm validation catches it and speaks the error

4. Test the sync demo moment:
   - With several unsynced records in queue, turn wifi back on
   - Confirm records appear in Supabase dashboard within 5 seconds
   - Confirm sync status dots turn green in History screen

5. Add a "Demo Reset" button hidden in settings (triple-tap the app title) that clears all SQLite records — for resetting between demo runs

6. Verify no TypeScript errors: run tsc --noEmit and fix all issues

7. Verify the app runs on a real physical device, not just simulator. Test on both iOS and Android if possible.

8. Document any hardcoded Supabase keys and replace with environment variables via expo-constants.
```

